# Service Layer Patterns

## Base Service Architecture

### StrapiService Base Class

All services should extend [StrapiService](mdc:strapi/services/strapi/strapi.service.ts):

```typescript
export class StrapiService {
  private strapiEndpoint: string | null = null;
  private apiToken: string | null = null;

  constructor() {
    this.strapiEndpoint = Deno.env.get("STRAPI_ENDPOINT") || null;
    this.apiToken = Deno.env.get("STRAPI_API_TOKEN") || null;
  }

  public get getStrapiEndpoint(): string {
    return this.strapiEndpoint || "";
  }

  public get getStrapiApiToken(): string {
    return this.apiToken || "";
  }
}
```

## Service Implementation Patterns

### Constructor Pattern

```typescript
class FormService extends StrapiService {
  private currentForms: IForm[] = [];
  private currentFormSlugs: string[] = [];
  private currentTime = new Date().toISOString();

  constructor() {
    super();
    this.loadCurrentForms();
  }

  private async loadCurrentForms(): Promise<void> {
    // Initialize service state
  }
}
```

### Method Organization

- **Public methods**: Business logic exposed to main.ts
- **Private methods**: Internal implementation details
- **Validation methods**: Data validation and sanitization
- **Utility methods**: Helper functions specific to the service

### Async Method Patterns

```typescript
public async processData(): Promise<void> {
  try {
    console.log("🚀 ~ Starting operation ⏳");
    
    // Setup
    const data = await this.loadData();
    const chunkSize = 10;
    let processed = 0;
    
    // Processing loop
    for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i += chunkSize) {
      const chunk = data.slice(i, i + chunkSize);
      const promises = chunk.map(item => this.processItem(item));
      
      await Promise.all(promises);
      processed += chunk.length;
      
      console.log(`📈 ~ Progress: ${processed}/${data.length} items processed`);
    }
    
    console.log("✅ ~ Operation completed");
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("❌ ~ Operation failed:", error);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Data Processing Patterns

### Chunked Processing

- Use small chunk sizes (1-10) for API operations
- Use larger chunks (100+) for file operations
- Process chunks in parallel with `Promise.all()`
- Add progress logging for long operations

### Batch Operations

```typescript
const promises = chunk.map(async (item) => {
  try {
    const result = await this.processItem(item);
    return { success: true, result };
  } catch (error) {
    return { success: false, error };
  }
});

const results = await Promise.allSettled(promises);
```

### State Management

- Load initial state in constructor
- Cache frequently accessed data
- Update state after successful operations
- Use private properties for internal state

## Validation Patterns

### Input Validation

```typescript
public validateInput(data: FormData): { errors: string[]; isValid: boolean } {
  const errors: string[] = [];
  
  if (!data.title) {
    errors.push("Title is required");
  }
  
  if (data.title && data.title.length > MAX_LENGTH) {
    errors.push(`Title too long: ${data.title.length}`);
  }
  
  return {
    errors,
    isValid: errors.length === 0
  };
}
```

### Data Transformation

```typescript
public async transformData(rawData: ICsvRawData): Promise<FormData> {
  const { result, errors } = await this.getFormData({ data: rawData });
  
  if (errors.length > 0) {
    throw new Error(`Data transformation failed: ${errors.join(", ")}`);
  }
  
  return result;
}
```

## Error Handling in Services

### Error Logging

```typescript
try {
  await this.performOperation();
} catch (error) {
  const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
  console.error(`❌ Operation failed:`, errorMessage);

  // Log to file
  await this.logError(errorMessage, context);

  throw error;
}
```

### Graceful Degradation

```typescript
const results = await Promise.allSettled(operations);
results.forEach((result, index) => {
  if (result.status === "rejected") {
    console.error(`❌ Operation ${index} failed:`, result.reason);
    // Continue processing other operations
  }
});
```

## Service Dependencies

### Dependency Injection

```typescript
class FormService extends StrapiService {
  constructor(
    private categoryService: CategoryService,
    private uploadService: UploadService,
  ) {
    super();
  }
}
```

### Service Communication

- Use other services through constructor injection
- Avoid circular dependencies
- Keep services loosely coupled
- Use interfaces for service contracts

## Export Pattern

```typescript
export const formService = new FormService();
```

## Configuration Integration

- Use [CONFIGURATION](mdc:strapi/config/settings.ts) constants
- Access environment variables through base service
- Use [enum.ts](mdc:strapi/config/enum.ts) for type safety
- Support different environments (dev/staging/prod)
